port%20and%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-i-made-switzerland-first-time-airbnb-restaurants-buses-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESwitzerland%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20let%20out%20an%20audible%20sigh.%20As%20someone%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20Montana%2C%20with%20nature%20and%20wildlife%20all%20around%2C%20mountains%20have%20always%20felt%20like%20home%20to%20me%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20a%20town%20with%20a%20different%20language%20and%20culture.%20In%20this%20small%20hamlet%20of%20under%205%2C000%20residents%2C%20I%20could%20breathe%20again.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20long%20list%20of%20things%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%20I%20began%20by%20making%20my%20way%20to%20the%20famous%20Benedictine%20Monastery%2C%20built%20in%201120%2C%20where%20monks%20still%20live%20and%20work.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20I%20bundled%20up%20and%20took%20a%20cable%20car%20to%20the%20top%20of%20Mount%20Titlis%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.switzerland-tickets.com%2Fmount-titlis%2Fcable-car%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20first%20revolving%20cable%20car%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20time%20of%20year%20it%20is%2C%20there's%20only%20one%20season%3A%20winter.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20walked%20across%20the%20highest%20suspension%20bridge%20in%20Europe%3B%20wandered%20through%20the%20glacier%20cave%2C%20illuminated%20and%20still%3B%20sat%20on%20the%20glacier%20chairlift%20to%20snap%20photographs%3B%20and%20took%20my%20place%20in%20line%20to%20go%20sledding%20at%20Glacier%20Park%2C%20where%20a%20large%20tourist%20family%20laughed%20and%20tossed%20snowballs%20at%20each%20other%2C%20making%20me%20painfully%20miss%20my%20three%20boys%20at%20home.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20brood%20would%20have%20loved%20to%20play%20in%20the%20snow%3B%20I%20had%20to%20fight%20back%20feelings%20of%20lonesomeness.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22995849ea-c10a-42bb-9dc5-f051bc416a2b%5C%22%3EThe%20older%20I%20get%2C%20the%20more%20obsessed%20I%20get%20with%20longevity%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20my%20body%20fully%20has%20become%20a%20priority%20as%20I%20age%2C%20so%20that%20was%20a%20must%20for%20this%20trip.%20The%20next%20couple%20of%20days%20were%20filled%20with%20outdoorsy%20escapades%2C%20where%20I%20hiked%20on%20numerous%20paths%20full%20of%20trailside%20cheese%20stands%2C%20wildflower-dotted%20mountainsides%2C%20and%20mooing%20cows.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20butterflies%20in%20my%20stomach%20on%20the%20via%20ferrata%2C%20a%20thrilling%20climbing%20route%20that%20uses%20fixed%20steel%20cables%2C%20ladders%2C%20and%20other%20systems%20to%20safely%20help%20you%20navigate%20steep%20and%20rocky%20terrain.%20At%20the%20top%2C%20I%20felt%20powerful%20and%20itty%20bitty%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rain%20poured%20down%20in%20sheets%20the%20day%20I%20went%20kayaking%20across%20Tr%C3%BCebsee%20Lake%2C%20an%20alpine%20loch%20at%20the%20foot%20of%20Titlis%20mountain%2C%20high%20above%20Engelberg%2C%20reached%20only%20by%20cable%20car%20or%20intrepid%20foot.%20With%20the%20lake%20completely%20to%20myself%2C%20I%20paddled%20around%20and%20surveyed%20the%20clouds%20as%20they%20seemed%20to%20pucker%20and%20blot%20out%20the%20mountains.%20The%20cacophony%20of%20sound%20was%20so%20great%20that%20I%20could%20only%20hear%20the%20shower%20and%20my%20own%20thoughts.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20closed%20my%20eyes%2C%20put%20one%20hand%20to%20my%20heart%2C%20and%20smiled.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2250a7c730-13c6-427b-a296-15c75d61f7f1%5C%22%3EI%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20see%20me%20as%20more%20than%20just%20a%20mom%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-solo-travel-mom-guilt-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThere%20was%20no%20guilt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20no%20desire%20to%20justify%20my%20choices%3B%20I%20simply%20felt%20delighted%20for%20making%20the%20resolution%20to%20take%20care%20of%