%2039%20miles%20outside%20the%20city%20between%20January%20and%20June%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20broker%20Hamptons%20International.%20That's%20six%20miles%20further%20than%20in%202019%20and%2065%25%20more%20than%20the%20typical%20first-time%20buyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFour%20years%20on%20from%20the%20pandemic%20and%20many%20city%20workers%20have%20settled%20into%20a%20new%20normal%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20going%20into%20the%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Aneisha%20Beveridge%2C%20head%20of%20research%20at%20Hamptons.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20bid%20to%20make%20their%20equity%20stretch%20further%2C%20movers%20continue%20to%20make%20longer%20distance%20moves%20out%20of%20the%20capital.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUK%20households%20are%20facing%20a%20mix%20of%20cost%20pressures%20triggered%20by%20higher%20interest%20rates%20and%20a%20cost-of-living%20squeeze.%20While%20home%20loan%20rates%20are%20steadily%20declining%20from%20the%2015-year%20high%20they%20reached%20in%202023%2C%20the%20number%20of%20UK%20mortgaged%20properties%20taken%20into%20possession%20rose%208%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%2025%25%20of%20households%20trading%20a%20London%20home%20for%20one%20outside%20the%20capital%20moved%20more%20than%20100%20miles%20away%20in%20the%20first%20half%2C%20significantly%20higher%20than%20the%2017%25%20average%20recorded%20between%202015%20and%202019.%20On%20average%2C%20London%20leavers%20are%20moving%2050%25%20further%20than%20they%20were%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20with%20high%20transaction%20costs%20reducing%20the%20number%20of%20shorter%2C%20more%20frequent%20moves%2C%20Hamptons%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGedling%20and%20North%20Somerset%20-%20two%20local%20authorities%20based%20in%20the%20Midlands%20and%20western%20England%2C%20respectively%20-%20have%20seen%20those%20looking%20to%20leave%20London%20more%20than%20double%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202024%20compared%20with%20the%20same%20period%20last%20year.%20London%20leavers%20accounted%20for%2048%25%20of%20people%20buying%20a%20home%20outside%20the%20capital%20between%20January%20and%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20a%20long-running%20rise%20in%20first-time%20buyers%20leaving%20London%20was%20restricted%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20as%20a%20steady%20decline%20in%20mortgage%20costs%20and%20lower%20house%20prices%20encouraged%20more%20prospective%20homeowners%20to%20buy%20in%20the%20capital.%20First-time%20buyers%20purchased%20a%20record%2048%25%20of%20homes%20sold%20in%20London%20between%20January%20and%20June%2C%20up%20from%2041%25%20in%202023%20and%2028%25%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20first-time%20buyers%20leaving%20the%20capital%20are%20increasingly%20seeking%20out%20more%20affordable%20areas%20closer%20to%20London%20rather%20than%20moving%20further%20afar.%20The%20share%20of%20first-time%20buyers%20leaving%20London%20for%20the%20countryside%20has%20halved%20from%20its%206%25%20peak%20in%202020.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLower%20mortgage%20payments%20have%20pulled%20the%20cost%20of%20buying%20back%20below%20renting%2C%20bringing%20relief%20to%20those%20looking%20for%20their%20first%20home%20in%20the%20capital%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamptons'%20Beveridge%20said.%20%26quot%3BFirst-time%20buyers%20with%20deeper%20pockets%20are%20looking%20again%20at%20London%2C%20choosing%20Clapham%20over%20Crawley%20and%20Wembley%20over%20Wycombe.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724635860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fchm6f0ho_londoners-housing-generic-bloomberg-_625x300_26_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhy-londoners-are-buying-houses-mil