20the%20user%E2%80%99s%20weight%20is%20being%20supported%20by%20the%20stick%3B%20based%20on%20that%2C%20we%20predict%20the%20likelihood%20of%20a%20fall%20and%20help%20diagnose%20potential%20problems%20or%20underlying%20conditions%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Rahi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20circuit%2C%20equipped%20with%20Bluetooth%20modules%2C%20transmits%20data%20to%20a%20laptop%2C%20generating%20real-time%20heat%20maps.%20These%20heat%20maps%20actually%20show%20which%20pressure%20points%20on%20the%20stick%20are%20bearing%20the%20most%20weight%2C%20giving%20an%20insight%20into%20what%20the%20problem%20could%20be%2C%20or%20what%20the%20chances%20of%20fall%20can%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20heat%20maps%20visually%20represent%20pressure%20points%2C%20with%20blue%20indicating%20low%20pressure%20and%20red%20indicating%20high%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiving%20an%20example%2C%20the%20students%20say%20that%20if%20the%20map%20shows%20high%20pressure%20on%20the%20left%20side%2C%20there%20is%20a%20probability%20that%20the%20user%20has%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20right%20knee%20or%20ankle.%20%E2%80%9CGenerally%2C%20when%20you%20have%20a%20problem%2C%20you%20tend%20to%20put%20less%20weight%20on%20that%20area%2C%20so%20that%20it%20pains%20less.%20You%20tilt%20more%20towards%20the%20opposite%20side%2C%20and%20hence%20the%20left%20side%2C%20which%20shows%20the%20highest%20pressure%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20explain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20students%20plan%20to%20develop%20a%20mobile%20app%20in%20the%20future%20to%20make%20this%20data%20more%20accessible%20to%20users.%20%E2%80%9CMany%20elders%20have%20lower%20body%20issues%20like%20osteoarthritis%2C%20osteoporosis%2C%20buckling%20knees%2C%20and%20hip%20fractures.%20Our%20device%20can%20predict%20falls%20in%20both%20standing%20and%20sitting%20positions.%20It%20detects%20stability%20in%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20gait%20and%20changes%20in%20balance%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Hriday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22